Positional Parameters

The shell parameters are numbered from 1 up
    # set one two three four five six seven eight nine ten eleven twelve
    # echo $1 $4 $9
    one four nine

Positionals are always parsed as decimal
    # echo ${11} ${011} ${0011}
    eleven eleven eleven

Unset positionals are just blank
    # recho "${42}"
    argv[1] = <>

Positionals are parsed soley as the digits
    # echo $7s
    sevens

Positionals are not settable via readonly or export
    # readonly 7=september      # SKIP plush TODO(mzero): fix!
    ! bad variable name
    ! not a valid identifier
    # export 7=september        # SKIP plush TODO(mzero): fix!
    ! bad variable name
    ! not a valid identifier

Shift parameters
    # set one two three four five six seven eight nine ten eleven twelve
    # shift
    # echo $*
    two three four five six seven eight nine ten eleven twelve
    # shift 3
    # echo $*
    five six seven eight nine ten eleven twelve
    # shift 0
    # echo $*
    five six seven eight nine ten eleven twelve

Shift errors codes
    # shift && echo ok || echo fail
    ok

    # shift 9                   # SKIP bash doesn't error, just doesn't shift!
    ! shift count too large
    ! shift

shift negative
    # shift -1
    ! shift count can't be negative
    ! shift

shift non-numeric
    # shift less
    ! shift argument not numeric
    ! shift

